data.description: Built in 1909 this 1.5 story home with 10 foot ceilings has generous sized rooms, 1/4 basement and detached, oversized, 2 car garage, 24 x 30, (720 square feet) offering ample storage, that boasts lots of character, quality and charm with many updates throughout! Most of the property, front and back, is secured with a 6 foot high chain link fence that allows added security if you have any pets or children. You can enjoy the huge porch across the front which allows for a nice sitting area.  The living room has been enhanced with a cozy, beautiful color changing, electric fireplace. There is an adjoining room that is separated by the massive, original solid wood, beautifully sculpted pocket doors and has currently been used as a third bedroom, but, could also make a wonderful family room, or, formal dining room. As you enter the home you will see the gorgeous original ornate wooden bannister that goes upstairs to a full size bathroom straight ahead and then off to the right and to the left are bedrooms complete with his and her closets. There are huge bay windows in one of the upstairs bedrooms. The main level consists of the kitchen area and full bathroom with laundry and the floors have been updated with a wood plank look. Basement access is off of the kitchen and is only used for storage. There is a sump pump downstairs to help eliminate dampness. The windows throughout this home are massive allowing the natural light and sunshine in and appear to have all been replaced. There are several areas in the house that have the beautiful original solid wood flooring. So many improvements worth mentioning have been done such as: the kitchen counter tops, sink and fixtures; the bathrooms and fixtures; HVAC in 2018; plumbing in 2018; furnace in 2018, water heater in 2018, new railings in 2020; new main level bathroom vent/exhaust fan in 2020 along with the flat roof over the bathroom, with the rest of the roof being estimated as 15 years old; and new ceiling fans throughout in 2021.
